The paper focuses on visual question answering (VQA), which involves both computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes a new approach for multi-modal feature fusion and fine-grained image and question representation, which involves machine learning techniques such as factorized bilinear pooling and co-attention learning. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.MM (Multimedia) are also likely sub-categories.
